President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Richard R. Verma as Deputy Secretary of State for Management and Resources. Verma currently serves as the Chief Legal Officer and Head of Global Public Policy at Mastercard. He previously held positions as the United States Ambassador to India and Assistant Secretary of State for Legislative Affairs during the Obama Administration. Verma has a background in national security, having served as National Security Advisor to United States Senator Harry Reid. He is also a veteran of the United States Air Force. Verma has received several awards and decorations for his service, including the Distinguished Service Medal from the Department of State. He currently serves on various boards, including The Ford Foundation and the National Endowment for Democracy.